Source: pggraph
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), cargo, clang
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/evokoa/pggraph

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pggraph
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pggraph, postgresql-graph
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Graph database extension for PostgreSQL
 pggraph adds graph traversal and query capabilities to PostgreSQL using pgrx.
 The Debian package follows the Pigsty distribution name pggraph, while the
 installed SQL extension, shared library, control file, and SQL payload are
 named graph.
